The paper deals with the design and analysis of a nano abnormality detection scheme in molecular nano-networks. It involves the use of sensor nano-machines (SNMs) and data-gathering nodes (DGN) to detect the presence of abnormal cells. The paper focuses on the analysis of the detection performance of the SNMs and the overall performance of the scheme in terms of probabilities of misdetection and false alarm. This involves the use of communication channels and the consideration of correlated Gaussian noise. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.BIO (Bioinformatics).
